```javascript
function printAsciiAndHexCodes() {
    for (let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
        let char = String.fromCharCode(i);
        let hex = i.toString(16).padStart(2, '0');

        console.log(`Character: ${char}, Hexadecimal Code: ${hex}`);
    }
}

printAsciiAndHexCodes();
```

This JavaScript program will generate and print out the ASCII character and hexadecimal codes for numbers 0 to 7f (127 in decimal). It loops through each number from 0 to 127, converts it to a character using the `String.fromCharCode()` method, then converts the same number to a hexadecimal string with `toString(16)`. The `padStart(2, '0')` method ensures that single digit hexadecimal codes are displayed with a leading zero, maintaining a consistent width. Each character and its corresponding hex code are then printed out using `console.log()`.
